item.title: ‘You have to define what killing is’: Jack Beaumont Pt. 2
item.description: At any one time, Jack Beaumont had five different identities. Different names, different families, different local cafes. Every morning, he woke up and became someone else. As a spy with the DGSE - the French CIA - he spent years infiltrating the worst humans on earth. Jack returns to I Catch Killers to talk about the cost of being a spy, having a licence to kill and the only thing that rattles him...
